Apple Cancellation

How to cancel a subscription on your iPhone or = iPad

  1. Open the Settings app.

  2. Tap your name.

  3. Tap Subscriptions.

  4. Tap the subscription.

  5. Tap Cancel Subscription. You might need to sc= roll down to find the Cancel Subscription button. If there is n= o Cancel button or you see an expiration message in red text, th= e subscription is already canceled.

Understanding JIRA =E2=80=93 JIRA Explained

How to build a JIRA? Explained.

(bolded items are template items/highlighted are to help you lo= cate the info for the bolder items) JIRA templates can be found here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1w_AzqYDlQKewb9nH5fvu4bWypNBBV7o2Xu= 0jZPKpDOk/edit

= Description of the issue: In your notes/given to you by the customer

= Email Address: In your notes/or from API

= User state (Limited Commercial, Essential, Premium, Ex Subsc= riber): In API under account info at the top of the page or if a s= ubscriber with a user package available you will enter the plan type (= essential vs limited commercials vs premium)

= Billing Platform: In API under user packages and source=

= Device ID: Comes from the customer directly from device (have customer o= pen P+ app on device, go to settings, then support within the app) 

= IP Address (https://whatismyipaddress.com/):&nb= sp;Comes from the customer directly from device (have customer o= pen P+ app on device, go to settings, then support within the app) or= listed in user viewing history (Conviva) in API

= Zip Code: API

= Show/Season/Episode # (Please provide specific Show and Episodes): From Customer

= Device Model & OS Version: From Customer (this is usually listed in the device settings= about section)

= App Version: Comes from the customer directly from device (have customer o= pen P+ app on device, go to settings, then support within the app) or= API user viewing history (Conviva)

= Connection (Wi-Fi/Ethernet/Hotspot/Cellular): From Customer

= Are you able to reproduce: This is a Yes if you can cause your system to have the same = issue and No if you cannot (also please ensure to notate what device= you used to replicate and if unable to replicate since you don=E2= =80=99t have the same device, note this)

= API URL: From Address Bar in browser while account is open in API (ex= ample below)

= https://customer.paramountplus.com/cust= omerProfile/USERID<= /span>

= Conviva Link: https://pulse.conviva.com/subscribers/?days=3D30&filter=3D4= 106&viewerId=3D= USER ID Replace User ID in Coviva link with the number at end of the AP= I link you just copy pasted above (above highlighted orange)

= Troubleshooting Steps Taken: Add all steps performed with customer over the phone=  

= Date this started occurring: Customer will tell you when the issues started 

= Speed Test results (for buffering/freezing issues; https://www.speedtest.net/): Always collect speed test results from website listed//Ensure = you are collecting upload, download, and ping rates as these are required to help narrow down the issue=
